Package de.gematik.bbriccs.fhir.coding

Interface WithSystem

All Known Subinterfaces:
WithCodeSystem, WithNamingSystem, WithStructureDefinition<T>
All Known Implementing Classes:
DeBasisProfilCodeSystem, DeBasisProfilNamingSystem, DeBasisProfilStructDef, HL7CodeSystem, HL7StructDef, UcumCodeSystem
public interface WithSystem
This base interface encapsulates the handling elements which are codeable with the FHIR coding system.

An implementation of the WithSystem interface can be one of

  • WithStructureDefinition representing a specific StructureDefinition
  • WithNamingSystem representing a specific NamingSystem
  • WithCodeSystem representing a specific CodeSystem
  • FromValueSet representing a specific ValueSet
Note: rather than implementing the WithSystem interface directly, you should always implement one of the above-mentioned interfaces.

  • Method Details

    • getCanonicalUrl

      String getCanonicalUrl()
      Get the canonical URL(1) of the system.

      Note(1): while the method is called getCanonicalUrl() resources/elements/values can be sometimes annotated with a system url which is not a URL at all. In fact, in most cases it should not be necessary to treat this value as a URL

      Returns:
      the canonical URL of the system

    • findFirstResource

      default Optional<org.hl7.fhir.r4.model.Resource> findFirstResource(List<org.hl7.fhir.r4.model.Bundle.BundleEntryComponent> bundleEntries)
      Find the first resource in the given bundle entries which matches the system.

      Example usage: Image you have a Bundle with a list of resources, and you want to find the first Patient resource which is profiled by KBV and has a definition KbvItaForStructDef.PATIENT implementing WithStructureDefinition and carrying the canonical URL system. 

      
 Bundle bundle = ... // which might contain the KBV-Patient Resource
 Optional<Patient> patient = KbvItaForStructDef.PATIENT
        .findFirstResource(bundle.getEntry())
        .map(Patient.class::cast);
      Parameters:
      bundleEntries - is the list of bundle entries to search in
      Returns:
      the first resource which matches the system

    • matches

      default boolean matches(org.hl7.fhir.r4.model.Bundle.BundleEntryComponent bundleEntry)
      Check if the given Bundle.BundleEntryComponent matches this system.

      Example usage: Image you have a custom "KbvBundle" class which extends from Bundle and you want to provide a convenient method to extract any Coverage resource which matches the KBV StructureDefinition defined in KbvItaForStructDef.COVERAGE wich itself is implementing WithStructureDefinition 

      
 public class KbvBundle extends Bundle {
   public List<Coverage> getCoverages() {
     return this.getEntry().stream()
         .filter(KbvItaForStructDef.COVERAGE::matches)
         .map(BundleEntryComponent::getResource)
         .map(Coverage.class::cast)
         .toList();
   }
 }
      Parameters:
      bundleEntry - to be checked if it matches the system
      Returns:
      true if the bundle entry matches the system
